{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:01:49.966543+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:kucSGR | successfully downloaded text file (SHA: a92a3a4b2ea3eaf6bb79b3123db671fd5c661936)", "id": "lc_2e914e93-5ec9-4497-9601-93d73a5d3cab"}, {"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:kucSGR | version: '3.8'\n| MCP:kucSGR | \n| MCP:kucSGR | services:\n| MCP:kucSGR |   web:\n| MCP:kucSGR |     build: .\n| MCP:kucSGR |     command: python main.py\n| MCP:kucSGR |     volumes:\n| MCP:kucSGR |       - ./:/usr/src/app/\n| MCP:kucSGR |     ports:\n| MCP:kucSGR |       - 11000:11000\n| MCP:kucSGR |     env_file:\n| MCP:kucSGR |       - ./.env\n| MCP:kucSGR |     depends_on:\n| MCP:kucSGR |       - postgres\n| MCP:kucSGR |       - redis\n| MCP:kucSGR |   postgres:\n| MCP:kucSGR |     image: postgres\n| MCP:kucSGR |     ports:\n| MCP:kucSGR |       - 5432:5432\n| MCP:kucSGR |     env_file:\n| MCP:kucSGR |       - ./.env\n| MCP:kucSGR |   redis:\n| MCP:kucSGR |     image: redis:alpine\n| MCP:kucSGR |     ports:\n| MCP:kucSGR |       - 6379:6379\n| MCP:kucSGR |     env_file:\n| MCP:kucSGR |       - ./.env", "id": "lc_d91cb9f8-c6d0-4c93-8337-491e7a6c9905"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "be1ea53c-7941-4c2e-9ce2-4d43dcef127c", "tool_call_id": "call_1711941929b849779edae5f5", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:01:49.976673+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:kucSGR | successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 7ddbdaff25796de88f0abe835585a5a5d83b4a5a)", "id": "lc_a7f64b0c-3ddd-4988-93ce-9c23534ca7f6"}, {"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:kucSGR | import logging\n| MCP:kucSGR | \n| MCP:kucSGR | import uvicorn\n| MCP:kucSGR | from fastapi import FastAPI\n| MCP:kucSGR | \n| MCP:kucSGR | from app.routes import router\n| MCP:kucSGR | from app.settings import settings\n| MCP:kucSGR | from app.db import db\n| MCP:kucSGR | \n| MCP:kucSGR | \n| MCP:kucSGR | app = FastAPI(title=settings.APP_TITLE)\n| MCP:kucSGR | \n| MCP:kucSGR | app.include_router(router, prefix=\"/api/v1\")\n| MCP:kucSGR | \n| MCP:kucSGR | \n| MCP:kucSGR | @app.on_event(\"startup\")\n| MCP:kucSGR | async def startup():\n| MCP:kucSGR |     await db.connect()\n| MCP:kucSGR | \n| MCP:kucSGR | \n| MCP:kucSGR | @app.on_event(\"shutdown\")\n| MCP:kucSGR | async def shutdown():\n| MCP:kucSGR |     await db.disconnect()\n| MCP:kucSGR | \n| MCP:kucSGR | \n| MCP:kucSGR | if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n| MCP:kucSGR |     \"\"\"\n| MCP:kucSGR |     Server configurations\n| MCP:kucSGR |     \"\"\"\n| MCP:kucSGR |     uvicorn.run(\n| MCP:kucSGR |         app=\"main:app\",\n| MCP:kucSGR |         host=settings.ALLOWED_HOST,\n| MCP:kucSGR |         debug=settings.DEBUG,\n| MCP:kucSGR |         port=settings.ALLOWED_PORT,\n| MCP:kucSGR |         reload=True,\n| MCP:kucSGR |         log_level=logging.INFO,\n| MCP:kucSGR |         use_colors=True,\n| MCP:kucSGR |     )", "id": "lc_3feb84c0-e6a2-4063-9a05-19e534038951"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "e8e34364-3ff2-4c0e-8e8b-4135769ad5b8", "tool_call_id": "call_f8fa9a92afa6472496c89035", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:01:49.977426+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:kucSGR | successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 6e90e2d5b8c4ddca40dea68ada13a608abb2f4f7)", "id": "lc_05334daf-0e95-422a-8bba-beac53cdc4a8"}, {"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:kucSGR | import logging\n| MCP:kucSGR | \n| MCP:kucSGR | import sqlalchemy\n| MCP:kucSGR | from databases import Database\n| MCP:kucSGR | from sqlalchemy.orm import sessionmaker\n| MCP:kucSGR | from sqlalchemy_utils import database_exists, create_database\n| MCP:kucSGR | \n| MCP:kucSGR | from .settings import settings\n| MCP:kucSGR | \n| MCP:kucSGR | \n| MCP:kucSGR | db = Database(settings.DB_URL)\n| MCP:kucSGR | metadata = sqlalchemy.MetaData()\n| MCP:kucSGR | engine = sqlalchemy.create_engine(settings.DB_URL, pool_size=3, max_overflow=0)\n| MCP:kucSGR | if not database_exists(engine.url):\n| MCP:kucSGR |     create_database(engine.url)\n| MCP:kucSGR | \n| MCP:kucSGR | LocalSession = sessionmaker(autocommit=False, autoflush=False, bind=engine)\n| MCP:kucSGR | \n| MCP:kucSGR | metadata.create_all(engine)\n| MCP:kucSGR | \n| MCP:kucSGR | \n| MCP:kucSGR | def get_db():\n| MCP:kucSGR |     \"\"\"\n| MCP:kucSGR |     A dependency for working with PostgreSQL\n| MCP:kucSGR |     \"\"\"\n| MCP:kucSGR |     try:\n| MCP:kucSGR |         db = LocalSession()\n| MCP:kucSGR |         yield db\n| MCP:kucSGR |     except Exception as e:\n| MCP:kucSGR |         logging.error(e)\n| MCP:kucSGR |     finally:\n| MCP:kucSGR |         db.close()", "id": "lc_de6aaa90-4341-4ee2-83f2-5d0f1fce004e"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "efbc66d0-1154-45c8-8ff6-e7a989c14ffc", "tool_call_id": "call_58254cf90d50483bbc844405", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:02:12.721114+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "In this FastAPI template, application settings are managed through a centralized `Settings` class in `app/settings.py` that reads directly from environment variables. Here's the breakdown:\n\n## Environment Variable Loading\n\nAll environment variables are loaded via Python's `os.environ.get()` method. In the Docker setup (`docker-compose.yml`), all three services (`web`, `postgres`, `redis`) share the same `.env` file, which is created from the `.example.env` template.\n\n## Database URLs\n\nThe database connection strings are **derived/composed** from multiple individual environment variables:\n\n```\nDB_USER     = environ.get(\"POSTGRES_USER\")      # e.g., \"sasori\"\nDB_PASSWORD = environ.get(\"POSTGRES_PASSWORD\")   # e.g., \"sasori\"\nDB_DB       = environ.get(\"POSTGRES_DB\")         # e.g., \"akatsuki\"\nDB_PORT     = environ.get(\"POSTGRES_PORT\")       # e.g., \"5432\"\nDB_HOST     = environ.get(\"POSTGRES_HOST\")       # e.g., \"postgres\"\n```\n\nThese are then assembled into connection URLs using f-strings:\n\n- **`DB_URL`**: `postgresql+psycopg2://{DB_USER}:{DB_PASSWORD}@{DB_HOST}:{DB_PORT}/{DB_DB}`\n- **`TEST_DB_URL`**: Same pattern but uses `POSTGRES_TEST_DB` (e.g., \"hebi\") for the database name.\n\nThe `app/db.py` module consumes `settings.DB_URL` to create both an async `Database` instance (for the app) and a SQLAlchemy engine (with pool_size=3).\n\n## Token Settings\n\nToken expiry times are **hardcoded constants**, not derived from environment variables:\n\n- **`ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRY_TIME`**: `60 * 30` = 1800 seconds (30 minutes)\n- **`REFRESH_TOKEN_EXPIRY_TIME`**: `60 * 24 * 365` = 525,600 minutes (1 year)\n\nOther JWT/auth-related settings are also static:\n- `JWT_ALGORITHM = \"HS256\"`\n- `PASSWORD_HASHER = CryptContext(schemes=[\"bcrypt\"], deprecated=\"auto\")`\n\n## Redis Configuration\n\nRedis settings have **default fallback values**:\n\n```python\nREDIS_HOST = environ.get(\"REDIS_HOST\", \"localhost\")  # defaults to \"localhost\"\nREDIS_PORT = environ.get(\"REDIS_PORT\", \"6379\")       # defaults to \"6379\"\n```\n\nIn the Docker environment, these are overridden via `.env` to point to the `redis` service name.\n\n## Other Key Settings\n\n| Setting | Source | Notes |\n|---------|--------|-------|\n| `ALLOWED_HOST` | `environ.get(\"ALLOWED_HOST\")` | Direct passthrough |\n| `SECRET_KEY` | `environ.get(\"SECRET_KEY\")` | Direct passthrough |\n| `DEBUG` | `bool(environ.get(\"DEBUG\"))` | String to bool conversion |\n| `ALLOWED_PORT` | `int(environ.get(\"PORT\"))` | String to int conversion |\n| `PAGE_SIZE` | Hardcoded `50` | Not env-configurable |\n\n## Summary\n\nThe pattern is straightforward:\n1. **Direct passthrough** for most settings (host, secret key, allowed host)\n2. **Derived composition** for database URLs (building connection strings from parts)\n3. **Hardcoded constants** for token expiry and pagination size\n4. **Default values** for Redis configuration", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 769, "prompt_tokens": 10651, "total_tokens": 11420, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 35, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 9088}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "mimo-v2.5-pro", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "8e8edc66557e4aa7a28e73dd0b7cdb40", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ead55-501a-7541-a4b9-0c21fdb8d8a3-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 10651, "output_tokens": 769, "total_tokens": 11420, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 9088}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 35}}}}]}}}
